title: "Papercraft: Origami Kraken"
categories:
- Makerspace
tags:
---
If you've ever been to the Scholar's Lab Makerspace, you have at one point or another seen Lionel. Lionel is our resident kraken and the mascot of the Makerspace. Through the Japanese art of origami, folding paper, you can bring Lionel to life and create your own paper kraken. All you need is a piece of paper. 

Fold in half 
Unfold
Fold in half other way
Unfold
Fold in half diagonally
Unfold
Fold in half diagonally other way
Unfold
Bend sides in, making a triangle
Bring edge of one flap up to the top
Repeat for all flaps
Unfold all flaps
Fold top down to middle
Unfold
Fold top down to middle on other side
Open one bottom flap
Fold down flap
Repeat for other side
Fold corner to midpoint
Unfold 
Fold corner again up to previous crease 
Unfold
Fold first crease the other way
Fold top section using the previous fold as a guideline
Unfold
Repeat with other side
Unfold flaps so you have a square section with all the creases
Fold the outer layers in
Continue going through the layers until flat
Repeat for other side
Fold the single flap section down
Fold back
Fold top part of single flap section so that end of point meets midway point
Fold up
Fold down
Flip it over
Fold edge towards middle
Unfold
Fold top side edge towards middle
Unfold and pinch edge and fold towards middle
Repeat for other side
Pull inside flap out and fold out
Repeat with other side
Flip to back, fold face area in
Fold flaps upward
Use something to make space in the eyes and fold them down
Bend center crease up
Bend flap on top down
Press leg inwards and fold out
Repeat with other legs
Shape the legs and head as you please to give it more 


